{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2532a90c-e049-419e-b8ea-59aca17d99ac","content":"On macOS, when a process crashes the system automatically generates a **crash report**. Look here:\n\n1. **User-level reports:**\n   `~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/`\n\n2. **System-level reports:**\n   `/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/`\n\nFiles are named like `YourAppName_YYYY-MM-DD-HHMMSS_machinename.ips`. You can also open **Console.app → Crash Reports** to browse them.\n\nFor a full **core dump**, run `ulimit -c unlimited` before launching your app. Core files land in `/cores/` (requires SIP adjustments on modern macOS).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"80e322f7-22bd-4cb7-8ea0-f37d79696e9d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT .NET app on macOS, without `createdump`. This is a general knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":217},"id":"9467a677-a004-4941-8c2a-9713c9f7cd6a","timestamp":"2026-04-08T01:00:57.318Z","parentId":"ca81a5d4-01d6-4b1e-af00-c48d805114aa"}
